data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0872c9cbfa96a57d0069c2ad651a70819688b3e6ecafab2a21","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":318,"text":"\n## [Paris, France](https://www.google.com/maps/search/Paris%2C+France?utm_source=openai)\n\n\nParis is the capital and largest city of France, located in the north-central part of the country along the Seine River. It serves as the nation's political, economic, and cultural center. ([britannica.com](https://www.britannica.com/place/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe name \"Paris\" is derived from the Parisii, a Celtic tribe that inhabited the area from the 3rd century B.C. ([countryreports.org](https://www.countryreports.org/country/france/capital-city.htm?utm_source=openai))\n\nKnown as the \"City of Light,\" Paris has been a major center of finance, diplomacy, commerce, culture, fashion, and gastronomy since the 17th century. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe city is home to iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower and the Louvre Museum, attracting millions of visitors each year. ([britannica.com](https://www.britannica.com/facts/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nAs of 2026, Paris has an estimated population of over 2 million within the city limits, with a metropolitan area population exceeding 13 million. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe city is also known for its temperate oceanic climate, with mild winters and warm summers. ([britannica.com](https://www.britannica.com/place/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nParis is divided into 20 administrative districts called arrondissements, each with its own unique character and attractions. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe city is governed by the Council of Paris, with Anne Hidalgo serving as the mayor. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Paris?utm_source=openai))\n\nParis is also a major hub for international organizations, including UNESCO and the International Chamber of Commerce. ([worldatlas.com](https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/what-is-the-capital-of-france.html?utm_source=openai))\n\nThe city's rich history, vibrant culture, and significant global influence make it a prominent and influential city worldwide. "}

